@doc
Katja Echo is a simple <a href="http://riemann.io" target="_blank">Riemann</a> server implementation written in Erlang. The source code can be found on <a href="https://github.com/katja-beam/katja_echo" target="_blank">GitHub</a>.

<a href="https://travis-ci.org/katja-beam/katja_echo" target="_blank"><img src="https://travis-ci.org/katja-beam/katja_echo.png" /></a>
<a href="https://coveralls.io/r/katja-beam/katja_echo?branch=master" target="_blank"><img src="https://coveralls.io/repos/katja-beam/katja_echo/badge.png?branch=master" /></a>

The public API of Katja Echo can be found in the {@link katja_echo} module.

The default configuration looks like this:

<pre><code>[
    {katja_echo, [
        {port, 5555},
        {pool, []},
        {callback, katja_echo}
    ]}
].</code></pre>

